MuleESB REST API with MySQL Example
====================

This example demonstrate the basis for putting a REST API with MySQL as your Database.


Usage: 
=======

GET:
===
GET: http://localhost:8081/users?username=admin
GET: http://localhost:8081/users

Example with CURL:  curl -i http://localhost:8081/users?username=admin


POST:
===
POST: http://localhost:8081/users

Example with CURL:  curl -d "username=jgonzalez" -X POST -i http://localhost:8081/users?username=jgonzalez

DELETE:
===
DELETE http://localhost:8081/users

Example with CURL: curl -X DELETE -i http://localhost:8081/users?username=jgonzalez


PUT:
===
PUT: http://localhost:8081/users?username=

 
